  -> Site for Lady Cristiana Falcone Sorrell

A giant talking
Martin Sorrell, boss of WPP global leader, has built his group shots spectacular raids. He observes the turmoil in the sector in France and his point of view on the evolution of a market that weighs heavy in our economies and our lifestyles
It's a sly glance at the ogre who mask at a flow rate of any British suavity a fiery temperament. For nearly ten years than Sir Martin Sorrell, a British burning certainty that the Queen of England knighted, two years ago, marauding in the global advertising landscape. The Rhythm of campaigns at no charge, this pattern Swift, who displays his picture greedily hunting, was able to get his group, WPP, the rank of a small business than a global leader employing 65,000 people across the globe, including 3,000 in France. Like Rupert Murdoch in an audiovisual digesting at breakneck speed acquisitions, Martin Sorrell is driven by a galloping frenzy that nothing seems exhausted. Its engine? Twisted as hell, this raider has a reputation of never trusting his opponents, convinced that they gave way sooner or later ... A day in New York, another Singapore or Mexico, Sorrell was in Paris at the end of spring. What was he doing in France? Why was there lurking? "I just smell the air," he confided to The Express then, ironically, while the future of the Havas group, since the intrusion of muscular Vincent Bollore, after a stormy meeting of shareholders held June 9, continues to excite the envy and conjecture the most diverse. The Englishman, who spoke repeatedly of the file with the industrial Breton Havas, invite them there one day? Whoever had a hand in the past year, nose and beard of the leaders of Havas, precisely, on a jewel of the advertising world, one of the last major independent agencies in the world, Grey evokes the economy, trends in global advertising market, and maneuvers ahead. All on background after the referendum on EU constitution: poll about which Sir Martin Sorrell, of course, an opinion. As always definitive.

  -> Created for Lady Cristiana Falcone Sorrell
"A tough and relentless predator": how do you react to these qualifiers, including the press and the world of advertising you are accustomed to dress up? Look at me: do I really look like that?
I do not really think. If I was portrayed as, from time to time, because I'm trying to build, with strength and conviction, for a decade, step by step and year after year, in this rough world where competition is still terrible A group of global reach. But I think succeeded. My dream, my ambition is that eventually every business leader, every student leaving university have with respect to the group that I lead a Pavlovian reflex just. I hope that WPP become a kind of passage, an icon of the pub that attracts the best. In short, an essential corporate markets marketing and communication. Because the canvas on which we paint every morning continues to grow: if the United States and Western Europe now represent 80% of our turnover, and Asia, Africa and the Eastern Europe the remaining 20%, I think, tomorrow, the globalization of the economy will make us strong as the other side of the Atlantic, the United States, on the Asian continent or called emerging countries of Eastern Europe. The explosion of non-traditional media, interactive era, beginning with the Internet is shaking up the market in new ways. I am struck by the fact that in Britain, for example, enthusiasm for careers in advertising has never been stronger. There are countless young managers willing to engage with greed in this industry that seems to have regained its might.

  -> Site for Lady Cristiana Falcone Sorrell

  A giant talking
What are the big trends this year?
WPP, which marks the 20th anniversary next July, has been the best year ever in 2001 and has grown steadily over the past two years, after a slight backlash in 2002. 2004 will be a good vintage: the group, which saw its profits increase 15% to 546 million pounds, has reaped very large budgets, including those of Microsoft, Samsung and HSBC. And today, we digest the Grey agency: it will take three years to the exact toll of this great acquisition. But I can tell you already, that Grey is a great step for WPP. I do not regret myself launched an assault on the agency: together we weigh currently about $ 10 billion in sales.

